package_name: Taj Mahal and Agra Fort Tour
description: Explore the majestic Taj Mahal and the historic Agra Fort, with insights into Mughal architecture and history.

package_name: Qutub Minar and Red Fort Discovery
description: A day tour to see Delhi’s iconic Qutub Minar and the UNESCO-listed Red Fort, including a cultural exploration of Old Delhi.
Visit the ancient rock-cut temples of Ajanta and Ellora, two UNESCO World Heritage sites famous for their intricate carvings and murals.
A guided tour of Fatehpur Sikri, the city built by Emperor Akbar, followed by a visit to the stunning Taj Mahal.
Discover the world-famous Khajuraho temples, known for their stunning architectural beauty and intricate sculptures.

package_name: Konark Sun Temple and Puri Beach
description: Explore the ancient Sun Temple at Konark, a UNESCO World Heritage site, and relax on the beaches of Puri.
Visit the iconic ruins of Hampi, a UNESCO-listed site, with its historic temples, markets, and royal enclosures.
Take a boat ride to the Elephanta Caves and discover the ancient rock-cut temples dedicated to Hindu gods.
Explore the living root bridges, caves, and waterfalls of Meghalaya, blending nature with the state’s rich cultural heritage.

package_name: Rani ki Vav and Modhera Sun Temple
description: Explore the intricate stepwells of Rani ki Vav and the Sun Temple at Modhera, showcasing India’s architectural heritage.
Visit Dhauli, the site of the Kalinga war, and take a serene boat ride on Chilika Lake to observe the unique bird sanctuary.

package_name: Jantar Mantar and City Palace Tour
description: A cultural journey through Jaipur, visiting the astronomical marvel of Jantar Mantar and the stunning City Palace.

package_name: Red Fort and Jama Masjid Tour
description: Explore the grandeur of the Red Fort and Jama Masjid, two iconic monuments that reflect the rich Mughal heritage of India.
Discover the ancient Bhimbetka rock shelters, showcasing prehistoric cave paintings that are over 30,000 years old.
Visit the grand Brihadeeswarar Temple and Gangaikonda Cholapuram, both UNESCO-listed for their architectural excellence.
